Out of sync resources does not necessarily indicate a bug in core... it means
the files in the file system have changed without the workspace knowing about
it.  Does it work with a new workspace.

The first log entry, "Could not load library: libcore_2_1_0b.so." is expected
since we don't currently ship a library for that architecture.  It's possible
that our existing natives could be recompiled as-is on this new architecture.
However, this library is only used as an optimization - if it is missing we fall
back to a Java-only solution that should work fine.
